@Deletirium So you've never personally experienced superhero fatigue, since you never liked the genre. Is it possible you're letting that bias through? I personally have always liked the genre as an extension of the action movie genre. But if you knew me you would regularly here me complaining about superhero movies, not because I have grown to dislike the genre, but because I dislike the many of the movies made in the genre.

I am not suggesting superhero fatigue doesn't exist, but I've certainly never met anyone in real life who has actually experienced it.

Edit: I should be more clear in saying that my point is, I don't think we can accurately determine the amount superhero fatigue contributes to declining popularity of superhero movies, until we get reliably strong entries in the genre again.

