@oBCHANo Worse comment in the thread.  Drinker is hardly 'far right' (unless you think something like 60%, if not more, of the country is 'far right').  Honestly, if you want to see a complete lack of thinking and logic, go hang out with some leftist (tell them how good their transition surgery was to see rather hilarious double speak as they are insulted but can't admit the truth of the situation). 
Concerning the money argument, two things can be true at once: it is correct movie tickets are expensive, but it has also been a factor since at least the 1990s (and, thus, not the main reason why the last few marvel movies failed to make lots of money).  Movie tickets being expensive has been a thing for at least 30+ years (and definitely a thing when the MCU started).  There will be some other movie genre soon that comes out and makes over a billion dollars, and those types of films will be all the rage for however many years.  Super hero films are like the Westerns of old - they made a lot of money at the time, but have started to fall out of favor with the general audience.  
I also find the argument that people don't go to movies because of the expensive concessions to be idiotic as nobody is forcing you to buy the outrageously expensive popcorn (again, this was an issue in the 1990s as well - the solution was, and still is, to not buy it). Nobody is not going to the movies because the popcorn is expensive.  They don't go because the cost of the tickets or the babysitter is expensive.

